in servicing missions until 2009,

102
00:05:37,756 --> 00:05:41,546
which is the last Hubble Space Telescope
servicing mission.

103
00:05:41,547 --> 00:05:47,341
You see a dramatic increase
in the spatial density of debris

104
00:05:47,594 --> 00:05:50,979
at the so-called
Sun-synchronous orbit altitude

