the total surface about 500 square meters.

131
00:07:18,262 --> 00:07:22,602
The likelihood of a collision
with very small debris

132
00:07:22,603 --> 00:07:27,299
of a size between 0.1 mm and 1 mm is 1,

133
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:31,555
which means that we have,
I would say, every day or even every week

134
00:07:31,556 --> 00:07:34,378
a collision with very small debris
which, of course,

135
00:07:34,379 --> 00:07:37,375
for the International Space Station
